title: Cops attacked as 300 crash house party
text:
Share on Twitter 
POLICE have arrested 11 people and responded to two drug overdoses following an out-of-control party in Lake Macquarie. 
Twenty-six police cars were called to Ida St in Charlestown about 8.20pm Friday night after a party was gatecrashed by about 300 revellers. 
A teenage brawl broke out soon after. Police were pelted with bottles and cans as they tried to break up the fight. 
A 17-year-old partygoer, who had arrived for a house party with some school friends, told radio station Hit 106.9 that the scene was “insane”. Officers arrest a youth after wrestling him to the ground. Picture: YouTube Source: Supplied 
“There were so many strangers,” she said. “There were crazy kids trying to fight police and yelling ‘f**k the cops’ as they sprinted across the road.” 
NSW Police said two teenage girls have been admitted to hospital suffering suspected drug overdoses. 
“A 17-year-old teenage boy was charged with affray, malicious damage to police vehicle and offensive behaviour,” a police statement said. 
“He was refused bail to appear at a court today. 
“A 27-year-old Marks Point man was charged with assault police, resist police, and possess prohibited drugs. 
“He was refused bail, to appear at Newcastle Local Court today.”
